<br>
Cats in Hats does not ruin the game for the rest of us. Please do not exaggerate the issue. The maximum amount of discomfort for anyone from this event is probably that Reeko will have to sit for another 6 days in Skyfire and attempt to get a force together earlier the next time.<br>
<br>
If anything, Cats in Hats has probably strengthened the resolve of everyone that supports the list and will most likely make it MORE difficult for them to attempt the same thing the next time, not less. It's funny the way things work. You think Gunther or TK won't be even quicker to respond next time?<br>
<br>
I care about this because I care about my community. I work hard enough to try and help enough people (e.g. you and your epic when I didn't even know you) that I feel like I have a right to ask these questions of CiH. I would help them if they needed it. Just because they don't doesn't make it any less true.<br>
<br>
Using blanket statements and generalizing the issue to the entire guild is not going to achieve the results I &quot;think&quot; you are trying to achieve. <br>
<br>
If anything it will just engender more of an &quot;us against them&quot; mentality. There is no &quot;us&quot; and there is no &quot;them.&quot; They are part of the same Server that we are. They grew up in levels just like we did and had to deal with the same issues we are.<br>
<br>
Having a guildleader state that the actions of some of his or her members is ok means a lot. That guildleader is expected to be the voice of his/her guild. When he speaks, he speaks for Roenyn, Seethur, Lern, Aakla and the rest of CiH.<br>
<br>
I am still bummed that this happened. CiH was welcome to participate. If anything, you had more resources to be able to get your clerics on the list faster than anyone else in the game.<br>
<br>
Grrr. Why set the tone like this? Do you remember what happened to Furor when he went around threatening blacklisting guild members that were griefing him on shard camps?<br>
<br>
Even Furor, who will never be hurting for ANYTHING in this game, decided that diplomacy would benefit him more. By working TOGETHER with the guilds, he was able to get into VT about 3x faster. <br>
<br>
I just don't get it.<br>
